controller_obligations:
The Controller shall:
(a) Ensure a valid legal basis exists for all personal data provided to the Processor, including obtaining and managing consent where required;
(b) Provide documented processing instructions and promptly notify the Processor of any changes;
(c) Conduct and maintain a Data Protection Impact Assessment for the processing activities covered by this agreement;
(d) Respond to data subject requests and inform the Processor of relevant obligations within 48 hours.

processor_obligations:
The Processor shall:
(a) Process personal data solely in accordance with the Controller's documented instructions, unless required by applicable law;
(b) Ensure that personnel authorised to process personal data are bound by written confidentiality obligations;
(c) Implement and maintain the technical and organisational measures specified in this agreement;
(d) Assist the Controller with data subject requests, data protection impact assessments, and supervisory authority consultations;
(e) Not engage additional sub-processors without prior specific written authorisation from the Controller;
(f) Make available all information necessary to demonstrate compliance and allow for audits.
